{
  "text": "N 0 is the Brunt-V\u00e4is\u00e4l\u00e4 frequency and h 0 \u03ed 2 km/d is the growth rate of the CBL. Q \u03fe 0 during the daytime (t sunrise \u03fd t \u03fd t sunset ), and Q \u03fd 0 during the night (t sunset \u03fd t \u03fd t sunrise ). When A \u03ed 0, the duration of the day is equal to the length of the night. We chose A such as to have a daytime of 14 hours and a nighttime of 10 hours, as during a summer day at 54\u040aN latitude. During the first day (t sunrise \u03fd t \u03fd t sunset ) the CBL, h D ( x, t), grows monotonically from sunrise to sunset [CITATION_1] :",
